        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 7 at 5:20PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 520 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Kenton, or 26 miles west of Boise City, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Black Mesa Park and Kenton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
